To generate a table of contents automatically in a LATEX document, you can use the `toc` package. Here's an example:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{toc}

\begin{document}

\tableofcontents

\chapter{Introduction}
\section{First Section}
\subsection{First Subsection}
\section{Second Section}
\subsection{Second Subsection}
\section{Third Section}
\subsection{Third Subsection}

\end{document}
```

In this example, the `toc` package is loaded at the beginning of the document, and the `\tableofcontents` command is used to generate the table of contents. The table of contents will automatically include the chapter and section headings in the document.

You can customize the table of contents by using the options provided by the `toc` package. For example, you can change the format of the page numbers, add a title to the table of contents, or include the list of figures and tables.

Here's an example of how to customize the table of contents:

```latex
